The paper focuses on deep pre-training and fine-tuning models for question answering, which falls under the natural language processing (NLP) domain. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses model compression and knowledge distillation, which are common techniques in machine learning and artificial intelligence, indicating that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Learning) are also likely sub-categories. The paper also involves information retrieval (IR) and deep learning (DL) techniques, which are relevant to cs.IR and cs.DL sub-categories, respectively.
